    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 1) Read & validate the receipt\nSlack file → download → multimodal LLM (OpenRouter, any vision model) → extract amount/vendor/category/date → check the policy in **Load Config**. Out-of-policy receipts are rejected in-thread; no manager is pinged.",
        "height": 200,
        "width": 1180,
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "node-026",
      "name": "Note 26",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        200,
        -120
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 2) Human-in-the-loop approval\nResolve the Slack user to their payout `rule_id`, then **Send and Wait** for the manager to Approve/Reject. Nothing moves without an explicit approval. The wait is capped at 1 day (see *Request Manager Approval* → Limit Wait Time); wire your own reminder/escalation if you want nudges.",
        "height": 220,
        "width": 700,
        "color": 5
      },
      "id": "node-027",
      "name": "Note 27",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        2080,
        380
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 3) Pay safely: dry-run, then fire\nOn approve: **dry-run** the rule (`simulation: true`) and only fire live if the simulation is clean. Live fire passes `executeAmount` (the receipt total, in cents) with a fresh `Idempotency-Key`. Then poll the execution for `transferIds` and confirm in-thread.",
        "height": 220,
        "width": 760,
        "color": 6
      },
      "id": "node-028",
      "name": "Note 28",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        3640,
        740
      ]
    },
